For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING LOCAL SALES AND
10 USE TAXES; TO REQUIRE THE DEPARTMENT OF FINANCE AND
11 ADMINISTRATION TO NOTIFY LOCAL GOVERNMENTS CONCERNING
12 SALES AND USE TAXES THAT ARE SET TO EXPIRE; AND FOR
13 OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING LOCAL SALES
18 AND USE TAXES; AND TO REQUIRE THE
19 DEPARTMENT OF FINANCE AND ADMINISTRATION
20 TO NOTIFY LOCAL GOVERNMENTS CONCERNING
21 SALES AND USE TAXES THAT ARE SET TO
22 EXPIRE.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 26-74-208(b)(3)(D), concerning the form of
27 the ballot for levying a county sales and use tax for capital improvements,
28 is amended to add an additional subdivision to read as follows:
29 (iii)(a) At least one hundred twenty (120) days
30 before the expiration of a sales and use tax levied under this subchapter,
31 the Department of Finance and Administration shall notify the county quorum
32 court of the county that levied the tax concerning the expiration of the
33 sales and use tax.
34 (b) The notification required under
35 subdivision (b)(3)(D)(iii)(a) of this section shall state the:
36 (1) Current expiration date of the sales
