5 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 26-74-308(b)(3)(D), concerning the form of
6 the ballot for levying a county sales and use tax for capital improvements,
7 is amended to add an additional subdivision to read as follows:
8 (iii)(a) At least one hundred twenty (120) days
9 before the expiration of a sales and use tax levied under this subchapter,
10 the Department of Finance and Administration shall notify the county quorum
11 court of the county that levied the tax concerning the expiration of the
12 sales and use tax.
13 (b) The notification required under
14 subdivision (b)(3)(D)(iii)(a) of this section shall state the:
15 (1) Current expiration date of the sales
16 and use tax; and
17 (2) Specific requirements under this
18 subchapter for extending the sales and use tax.
19
20 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 26-74-603(c), concerning the call for a tax
21 election for a county sales and use tax for capital improvements of a
22 community college, is amended to add an additional subdivision to read as
23 follows:
24 (5)(A) At least one hundred twenty (120) days before the
25 expiration of a sales and use tax levied under this subchapter, the
26 Department of Finance and Administration shall notify the county quorum court
27 of the county that levied the tax concerning the expiration of the sales and
28 use tax.
29 (B) The notification required under subdivision (c)(5)(A)
30 of this section shall state the:
31 (i) Current expiration date of the sales and use
32 tax; and
33 (ii) Specific requirements under this subchapter for
34 extending the sales and use tax.
35
